refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolin_array mixedneedle arrayhaystack boolstrict
Busca la needle (aguja) en el haystack (pajar).

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Devuelve &true; si la needle se encuentra en el array,
 &false; de lo contrario.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     4.2.0

      needle quizá no es un array.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Ejemplo de in_array


<?php
$os = array("Mac", "NT", "Irix", "Linux");
if (in_array("Irix", $os)) {
    echo "Got Irix";
}
if (in_array("mac", $os)) {
    echo "Got mac";
}
?>




     La segunda condición falla porque in_array
     es sensible a mayúsculas, así que el programa 
     The second condition fails because in_array
     is case-sensitive, so the program anterior mostrará:



Got Irix







    Ejemplo de in_array en modo estricto


<?php
$a = array('1.10', 12.4, 1.13);

if (in_array('12.4', $a, true)) {
    echo "'12.4' found with strict check\n";
}

if (in_array(1.13, $a, true)) {
    echo "1.13 found with strict check\n";
}
?>


    &example.outputs;


1.13 found with strict check







    in_array con un array como aguja


<?php
$a = array(array('p', 'h'), array('p', 'r'), 'o');

if (in_array(array('p', 'h'), $a)) {
    echo "'ph' was found\n";
}

if (in_array(array('f', 'i'), $a)) {
    echo "'fi' was found\n";
}

if (in_array('o', $a)) {
    echo "'o' was found\n";
}
?>


    &example.outputs;


  'ph' was found
  'o' was found
